    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are positioned for a high-ceiling output today, anchored by **Yordan Alvarez** (84.61) and **Junior Caminero** (78.33). **Yordan Alvarez** remains the premier play due to his elite 0.393 xwOBA and a favorable matchup against Hancock, while **Junior Caminero** benefits from the highest SP_xERA on the board (5.74) against Gil, negating the minor park penalty. We also see significant value in **Christian Yelich**, who draws a 74.33 efficiency score; his dynamic platoon edge against Irvin is substantial, yielding a 13% boost that elevates him well above his base projection.\n\nOur primary stolen base threats remain a tactical focus, with **Trea Turner** (65.63), **Caleb Durbin** (62.59), and **Hyeseong Kim** (59.95) serving as our engine room. **Hyeseong Kim** is particularly interesting today; despite a lower batting order slot, the combination of a favorable SP delivery profile\u2014which has been identified as highly susceptible to the swipe\u2014and a wind-aided environment keeps his efficiency within our starting threshold. Conversely, we have sidelined **Josh Smith** (53.82) despite his strong 14% platoon edge against Glasnow. While **Josh Smith** was the strongest consideration for the bench, the extreme efficiency of the starting outfield prevented his inclusion; he remains our primary pivot should any late-inning defensive replacements or weather delays occur.\n\nRisk mitigation is paramount today, specifically regarding **Chase Meidroth** (55.14). While his leadoff spot and platoon advantage are encouraging, the 31% rain risk in his matchup against Bubic necessitates a close watch; we have identified him as the most vulnerable starter should the forecast worsen. We are also proceeding with caution regarding **Logan O'Hoppe** (35.57) and **Victor Scott II** (35.39), both of whom are firmly below our 40.0 floor due to matchups against elite arms (Burns and Early, respectively). We are prioritizing the preservation of daily efficiency caps by keeping them benched, relying on the proven production of **Dillon Dingler**, **Colt Keith**, **Kazuma Okamoto**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, and **Kyle Schwarber** to navigate the middle of our lineup against their respective right-handed opponents.",
